			<h4>DRUG USAGE OF LGBT COMMUNITIES</h4>
			<p>Evidence suggests that, LGBT community are more likely to use tobacco and a range of illicit drugs. Estimates from the 2019 NDSHS indicate that daily smoking among LGBT people has steadily declined from 28% in 2010 to 16% in 2019 (AIHW 2020). However, LGB people are still 1.5 times as likely to smoke daily as heterosexual people.</p>
			<p>Illicit usage of drugs among LGB people has steadily increased from 31.8% in 2010 to 36% in 2019</p>
			<p>Switch between Heterosexual and Homosexual community to compare the drug usage</p>
